# WKExtendedRuntimeSessionState.notStarted

**Case**

The app has not yet started or scheduled the session.

## Declaration

```swift
case notStarted
```

## Discussion

When you instantiate a new session, it stays in the [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKExtendedRuntimeSessionState/notStarted] state until you call the session’s [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKExtendedRuntimeSession/start()] or [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKExtendedRuntimeSession/start(at:)] method.

## Session States

- **WKExtendedRuntimeSessionState.scheduled**: The app has scheduled the session to run at a future date.
- **WKExtendedRuntimeSessionState.running**: The session is actively running.
- **WKExtendedRuntimeSessionState.invalid**: Either the session has encountered an error, or it has stopped running.
